text: Moskovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Nauruzovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 409 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 69 km from Uchaly, 9 km from Nauruzovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Moskovo, Uchalinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
